            "answer_text": "First of all, Arab is not a race, it's the regional people of middle eastern countries, they're mostly semites mixed with whites. Countries such as Afghanistan, Iran, Palestine, Syria, and Turkey are considered white or Aryan. They're the descendants of Europeans who migrated several thousand years ago. Although some of them might have darker skin due to intermarriage with Arabs, Asians or Dravidians (Native asian Indians). In Kabul (Afghanistan's capital), the race is really mixed, you might find less Aryans because of its diversity, but in other regions it's mostly white. I am from east Afghanistan, Nangarhar, I had dark ginger hair when I was born, but it's now dark brown, and I have hazel eyes. My little brother was born pure blonde, but now he is dark brown too with brown eyes, pretty weird huh? It's funny how some people call us browns, mainly because of hatred and racial superiority notions, but that's not true. UPDATE: The term Aryan may be used to refer to a light skinned person of Iranic/Persian descent due to the heritage associated. You cannot call any Caucasian person Aryan; having a fair skin, or European genetics does not mean that person is Iranic. ",
