            },
            "answer_text": "All racial classifications are social constructs, but \"Caucasian\" is a racist term and has fallen out of favor to be used by anthropologists. The term is a racial classification developed by anthropologists in the 19th century who asserted that people of this \"ethnicity\" were descended from a tribe in the mountainous region in southeastern Europe and southwestern Asia that lies between the Black and Caspian seas. That belief has been widely discredited. So, no, they are not \"Caucasian\", as they did not come from the Caucasus region. And neither are most people of European descent. ",
